WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:03.623
Previously on "how to get away
with murder"...

00:03.624 --> 00:04.924
No offense. I think i liked
Rudy's setup better.
Rudy?

00:04.925 --> 00:06.086
Yeah, he's the freak
who lived here before you.

00:06.087 --> 00:07.297
Come on.
We had fun.

00:07.298 --> 00:08.468
You had fun.

00:08.469 --> 00:10.180
I was drunk and desperate.

00:10.181 --> 00:13.053
Rebecca goes to trial
unless we get the charges
against her dismissed.

00:13.054 --> 00:16.096
We have to prove that my husband
murdered Lila stangard.

00:16.097 --> 00:17.137
To allow this trial to proceed

00:17.138 --> 00:20.060
would be a gross miscarriage
of justice.

00:20.061 --> 00:21.561
Reporter:
Miss sutter, how does it feel

00:21.562 --> 00:22.982
to have the charges
against you dropped?
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

00:22.983 --> 00:25.065
Whatever his wife told you,
my brother is no murderer.

00:25.066 --> 00:26.947
Your sister-in-law's in town.

00:39.660 --> 00:41.622
[ Birds chirping ]

00:49.670 --> 00:53.013
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

00:56.056 --> 00:57.057
[ Beep ]

01:17.748 --> 01:20.079
[ Horns honking ]

01:20.080 --> 01:21.201
[ TV chatter ]

01:21.202 --> 01:25.205
Crowd: 6, 5,

01:25.206 --> 01:28.798
4, 3, 2, 1.

01:28.799 --> 01:31.211
Happy new year!

01:31.212 --> 01:33.764
[ Cheers and applause ]

01:34.305 --> 01:35.805
Wes: I'm so sorry.

01:35.806 --> 01:38.057
Annalise: Don't be.

01:38.058 --> 01:40.221
[ Bell tolls ]

01:45.776 --> 01:48.318
Bonnie:
Hi. How was your trip?

01:48.319 --> 01:49.939
Where is she?

01:49.940 --> 01:51.192
Upstairs.

02:02.122 --> 02:04.123
Hi.

02:04.124 --> 02:07.126
The Petersons still have
that swing set

02:07.127 --> 02:09.128
that Sam and i used to play on
when we were kids,

02:09.129 --> 02:11.090
even though their own children
moved out...

02:11.091 --> 02:12.512
What?...
30 years ago.

02:12.513 --> 02:15.556
Mrs. Peterson is still there.
Garrett died last fall.

02:17.017 --> 02:19.018
You've been avoiding me.

02:19.019 --> 02:20.220
No.

02:20.221 --> 02:22.222
Well, you haven't answered
my phone calls.

02:22.223 --> 02:25.064
Well, i went home.
I had to get my head together.

02:25.065 --> 02:28.608
To your mother's house.
Bonnie said.

02:28.609 --> 02:30.270
How is she?

02:30.271 --> 02:32.483
She's good.

02:34.365 --> 02:36.035
I can't remember the last time

02:36.036 --> 02:37.697
Sam mentioned
that you visited her.

02:37.698 --> 02:41.040
Well, it's been a while.

02:41.041 --> 02:43.283
Annalise,
can we please not do this?

02:43.284 --> 02:45.375
I don't know what you mean.

02:45.376 --> 02:47.707
Can you at least tell me
if you're concerned about him?

02:47.708 --> 02:49.789
Of course.
Then why leave?

02:49.790 --> 02:50.880
When a person goes missing...

02:50.881 --> 02:52.171
"fled," you mean?

02:52.172 --> 02:54.634
Either way, you don't leave.
You stay. You put up posters.

02:54.635 --> 02:56.506
But you stay so that you're
there when they come back.

02:56.507 --> 02:58.097
He's not coming back.
How do you know that?

02:58.098 --> 03:00.510
He killed a girl.
He doesn't want to go to jail.

03:00.511 --> 03:03.012
How do you know?
Did he tell you?

03:03.013 --> 03:05.014
The detectives say
that you confronted him,

03:05.015 --> 03:06.476
but he didn't confess anything.

03:06.477 --> 03:08.608
Would you?
If you were my wife

03:08.609 --> 03:11.070
and a defense attorney, yeah,
you bet i would.

03:11.071 --> 03:13.443
Well, you're not a killer.
He is.

03:13.444 --> 03:16.736
What about foul play?

03:16.737 --> 03:18.117
Why isn't that the first thing
you think of...

03:18.118 --> 03:20.780
Foul play, that...
That maybe he's been hurt?

03:20.781 --> 03:23.533
None of this makes any sense,
Annalise.

03:23.534 --> 03:25.495
Did you know
i-i was with him

03:25.496 --> 03:28.207
the day after that girl
was killed... Lila.

03:28.208 --> 03:30.380
We spent the entire
labor day weekend together.

03:30.381 --> 03:33.092
We... we went over...
We had lobsters at hemingways,

03:33.093 --> 03:37.297
and he helped fix the screen
door on my front porch,

03:37.298 --> 03:38.468
and we talked about you,

03:38.469 --> 03:40.470
about how much he wanted
that new job at Yale,

03:40.471 --> 03:42.101
and how he really thought

03:42.102 --> 03:43.473
that a fresh start
would be really, really good

03:43.474 --> 03:45.685
for the both of you.

03:45.686 --> 03:48.688
How could he have done
all those little things

03:48.689 --> 03:51.190
a-after he had just strangled
a girl to death?

03:51.191 --> 03:54.153
I don't know.
People don't make sense.

03:54.154 --> 03:55.485
W-what is this?

03:55.486 --> 03:56.776
[ Sighs ]

03:56.777 --> 03:58.157
That's the evidence
that i presented to the court

03:58.158 --> 03:59.949
to prove that
he killed that girl.

03:59.950 --> 04:01.281
You read it,

04:01.282 --> 04:03.663
and then you'll understand
what I've been going through.

04:03.664 --> 04:06.416
Whatever's in that box,
that's not my brother.

04:06.417 --> 04:08.459
He is not the man
we thought he was.

04:32.483 --> 04:34.233
Connor:
Hey there, killer.

04:34.234 --> 04:36.606
Funny.

04:36.607 --> 04:38.398
First day of a new semester.

04:38.399 --> 04:40.610
It's all so exciting, isn't it?

04:40.611 --> 04:42.992
Hey. Oh, god.

04:42.993 --> 04:45.535
Thank god you're both here.

04:45.536 --> 04:47.407
I was... i was getting
really anxious.

04:47.408 --> 04:49.369
Why? Are you worried that
i finally went to the police

04:49.370 --> 04:51.170
without you and waitlist
keeping an eye on me?

04:51.171 --> 04:53.333
Connor...

04:53.334 --> 04:54.874
Happy new year.
How was everyone's break?

04:54.875 --> 04:56.836
What is that?
It's a fake.

04:56.837 --> 04:59.008
I bought it with cash at
a jewelry mart in Chinatown.

04:59.009 --> 05:01.050
So, did everyone
have a nice holiday?

05:01.051 --> 05:02.972
Yeah.
Um...

05:02.973 --> 05:04.344
[ Chuckles ]
Well, mine was great.

05:04.345 --> 05:06.185
Aiden and i spent most of it in
east Hampton with his parents,

05:06.186 --> 05:07.557
then went to the mayor's
new year's party

05:07.558 --> 05:09.138
at Gracie mansion.

05:09.139 --> 05:10.930
Is there any news
about the sister?

05:10.931 --> 05:13.102
Did Annalise scare her back
to Boston yet,

05:13.103 --> 05:15.194
or did she just kill her?

05:15.195 --> 05:17.066
What are you talking about?

05:17.067 --> 05:18.858
Sam's sister.

05:18.859 --> 05:20.740
She got here
right before the break.

05:20.741 --> 05:23.653
She went to the police, said
she didn't believe any of it.

05:23.654 --> 05:26.706
She at least told you, right?

05:26.707 --> 05:28.248
No.

05:29.209 --> 05:31.541
[ Door opens, closes ]
Annalise:
Welcome back, everyone.

05:31.542 --> 05:33.413
Vacation is over.

05:33.414 --> 05:36.005
This is how to get away with
murder, the second semester,

05:36.006 --> 05:38.628
where things get even harder
than the first.

05:38.629 --> 05:40.881
[ Indistinct conversations ]

05:42.723 --> 05:44.634
Wes:
Why didn't you tell me?

05:44.635 --> 05:46.095
I didn't think
you needed to know.

05:46.096 --> 05:48.347
It's his sister. How would
i not need to know that?

05:48.348 --> 05:49.849
If i don't tell you
these things,

05:49.850 --> 05:51.020
it's because they're not things

05:51.021 --> 05:52.732
that you need to concern
yourself with.

05:52.733 --> 05:54.104
You have enough on your plate.

05:56.066 --> 05:58.438
How is she?

05:58.439 --> 06:00.780
Good.

06:00.781 --> 06:03.573
And you?
How are you?

06:03.574 --> 06:05.154
I'm tired.

06:05.155 --> 06:06.986
I can imagine.

06:06.987 --> 06:08.578
[ Knock on door ]

06:08.579 --> 06:12.082
Come in!

06:13.704 --> 06:15.495
We've got a walk-in
who claims she needs a lawyer

06:15.496 --> 06:17.046
for a d.U.I. Incident.

06:17.047 --> 06:18.377
You think it's press?

06:18.378 --> 06:19.919
Rubbernecker, more likely.

06:19.920 --> 06:22.712
Do you want me
to get rid of her?

06:22.713 --> 06:26.176
No. We can use some fun
around here.

06:30.220 --> 06:31.811
What precinct gave you
the d.U.I.?

06:31.812 --> 06:34.313
Excuse me?
D.U.I.S are issued

06:34.314 --> 06:36.726
with paperwork from the precinct
that pulled you over.

06:36.727 --> 06:39.479
You don't have it?

06:39.480 --> 06:41.150
Can we talk alone?

06:41.151 --> 06:42.822
No, because i don't believe you.

06:42.823 --> 06:45.154
Have you got
a good enough look yet

06:45.155 --> 06:47.196
at the house where the middleton
strangler lived?

06:47.197 --> 06:49.158
God, i missed this place.

06:49.159 --> 06:51.160
No, that's not why i...

06:51.161 --> 06:52.742
I don't care
about what your husband did.

06:52.743 --> 06:53.833
I'm here for you.

06:53.834 --> 06:54.834
I see.

06:54.835 --> 06:55.995
So you want to see the freak

06:55.996 --> 06:57.416
that sold out her husband
up close, huh?

06:57.417 --> 06:58.998
No, i don't think
you're a freak.

06:58.999 --> 07:01.130
I...

07:01.131 --> 07:03.133
I want to do what you did.

07:04.715 --> 07:09.098
I'm no role model.
You need to leave.

07:09.099 --> 07:10.510
Please.
I don't have anybody else.

07:10.511 --> 07:11.641
That's not my problem.

07:11.642 --> 07:13.222
I think you're gonna
want to take my case.

07:13.223 --> 07:14.474
I've already decided i don't.

07:14.475 --> 07:18.228
My husband's holding two girls
captive in our basement.

07:28.989 --> 07:31.200
Rebecca: Best Christmas ever.
[ Sighs ]

07:31.201 --> 07:33.412
Don't have to eat dry Turkey
or pretend that uncle ray

07:33.413 --> 07:36.035
isn't ripped on scotch and
looking at us inappropriately.

07:36.036 --> 07:37.997
What's that?

07:37.998 --> 07:39.999
Christmas card for Rudy.

07:40.000 --> 07:42.131
[ Siren wails in distance ]

07:42.132 --> 07:43.342
Hmm. Weird.

07:43.343 --> 07:45.545
Why wouldn't his relatives know
he doesn't live here anymore?

07:45.546 --> 07:46.846
I don't know.

07:46.847 --> 07:49.008
Maybe he's like us.

07:49.009 --> 07:51.010
Sucky family.

07:51.011 --> 07:53.012
He ever say that to you?
No.

07:53.013 --> 07:54.644
I hardly ever talked to him.

07:54.645 --> 07:56.225
[ Sniffs ]

07:56.226 --> 07:58.437
Let's... Open it.

07:58.438 --> 07:59.809
[ Groans ]

07:59.810 --> 08:02.021
No.
All right.

08:02.022 --> 08:06.065
Oh, it's from his grandma!

08:06.066 --> 08:07.947
Oh, and she's very generous.

08:07.948 --> 08:10.199
We can get beer with dinner now.

08:10.200 --> 08:13.072
She'll think he still lives here
unless we return it.

08:13.073 --> 08:16.205
You did better last night.

08:16.206 --> 08:19.118
I only had to wake you once.

08:19.119 --> 08:21.792
[ Sighs ] I'm sorry.

08:23.584 --> 08:26.796
Let's have ice cream
for breakfast.

08:26.797 --> 08:28.679
I freaking love
an orphan's Christmas.

08:36.266 --> 08:40.139
Jackie: I ran away when
i was 16, slept on the street.

08:40.140 --> 08:43.903
He said he would look out
for me.

08:43.904 --> 08:47.486
So we got married,

08:47.487 --> 08:49.739
but i could never get pregnant.

08:49.740 --> 08:52.281
Then he showed up with Rachel,

08:52.282 --> 08:55.915
and i didn't know what to do.

08:55.916 --> 09:01.621
I just knew i didn't want him
to hurt her the way he hurt me.

09:01.622 --> 09:03.583
Then Lynn came.

09:03.584 --> 09:08.047
She's pregnant again,
about to deliver.

09:08.048 --> 09:12.261
Last time, the baby died.
So this time...

09:12.262 --> 09:15.635
That's why I'm here.

09:15.636 --> 09:19.849
That can't happen again.

09:19.850 --> 09:21.020
Annalise:
Call the d.A.

09:21.021 --> 09:23.773
Tell them that we want to make
a plea deal.

09:23.774 --> 09:24.984
She's helping lock girls
in a basement.

09:24.985 --> 09:26.525
Why would
we want to protect her?
Did you hear her?

09:26.526 --> 09:28.988
She was 16 when she met him.

09:28.989 --> 09:30.359
She's a victim
of his abuse, too.

09:30.360 --> 09:32.191
But she's an adult now

09:32.192 --> 09:35.034
who held those two girls captive
in her own house.

09:35.035 --> 09:36.747
And she's finally doing
the right thing.

09:38.458 --> 09:39.869
What?

09:39.870 --> 09:41.831
Have none of you ever done
anything bad

09:41.832 --> 09:43.163
that you need a lawyer for?

09:45.465 --> 09:49.088
Sometimes your client
wants to plead guilty.

09:49.089 --> 09:51.170
And it doesn't happen often,
but when it does,

09:51.171 --> 09:52.762
you have to make sure
you get them

09:52.763 --> 09:54.343
the best plea deal possible.

09:54.344 --> 09:55.594
Galvinson:
What are you looking for?

09:55.595 --> 09:58.387
Accessory after the fact,
no jail time,

09:58.388 --> 10:01.100
treatment for medical
and psychological conditions.

10:01.101 --> 10:02.221
Well, that's gonna be hard

10:02.222 --> 10:04.353
without even giving us her name,
Annalise.

10:04.354 --> 10:06.355
There are two girls
rotting in a basement,

10:06.356 --> 10:07.987
one of whom's
about to give birth

10:07.988 --> 10:10.149
if that man doesn't beat her
to death first.

10:10.150 --> 10:12.361
Give us a deal.
Then we bring her in.

10:12.362 --> 10:15.785
If the d.A. Agrees to the terms
of the plea deal,

10:15.786 --> 10:17.947
then it's your job to make sure

10:17.948 --> 10:20.539
that every word
out of your client's mouth

10:20.540 --> 10:22.581
is an element that you use
in their defense.

10:22.582 --> 10:26.165
I did what i could
to protect them,

10:26.166 --> 10:28.167
cooked for them,
cleaned their clothes.

10:28.168 --> 10:30.589
I loved them...

10:30.590 --> 10:33.212
In spite of him.

10:33.213 --> 10:34.593
Of course,
there's no guaranteeing

10:34.594 --> 10:37.346
that the prosecutor will keep up
their end of the bargain,

10:37.347 --> 10:40.139
which is why you record
everything your client says

10:40.140 --> 10:41.811
in the room.

10:41.812 --> 10:44.433
Last time, he wouldn't let us go
to a hospital,

10:44.434 --> 10:46.475
and our little girl
was stillborn.

10:46.476 --> 10:48.729
I can't let that happen again.

10:50.440 --> 10:52.031
Lynn deserves to keep this one.

10:52.032 --> 10:53.863
Get down!
[ Groaning ]

10:53.864 --> 10:57.117
I need someone
to know the truth...

10:58.158 --> 11:00.660
so the girls
can finally be safe.

11:01.702 --> 11:03.492
They deserve to be safe.

11:03.493 --> 11:06.996
[ Both sobbing ]

11:06.997 --> 11:08.708
[ Indistinct conversations ]

11:08.709 --> 11:10.050
Annalise...

11:11.421 --> 11:14.173
I was just meeting
with detective Amos.

11:14.174 --> 11:15.344
He mentioned that you were here,

11:15.345 --> 11:18.057
working on your
"house of horrors" case.

11:18.058 --> 11:19.258
Have you looked
at the evidence yet?

11:19.259 --> 11:21.100
Making my way through it.

11:21.101 --> 11:23.102
Well, once you do,
let me know what you think.

11:23.103 --> 11:25.014
They have a lead on Sam.

11:25.015 --> 11:28.607
A police officer's wife called
from upstate New York

11:28.608 --> 11:30.610
and said she thinks she saw him
at a rest stop.

11:33.113 --> 11:36.156
No one told you?

11:38.028 --> 11:39.238
No.

11:39.239 --> 11:42.872
Right.

11:42.873 --> 11:46.536
I guess they think you have
your hands full with your case.

11:48.288 --> 11:50.670
I'll talk to Amos,
see what he knows.

11:52.172 --> 11:54.594
Sure.

12:05.766 --> 12:07.056
Jorge:
No, no, no, no, no.

12:07.057 --> 12:08.227
I lost the holiday golf
classic under protest.

12:08.228 --> 12:10.309
Scott springer...
City commissioner springer.

12:10.310 --> 12:12.231
Yes. He kicked the ball
to get a better lie.

12:12.232 --> 12:13.903
But i didn't
want to say anything

12:13.904 --> 12:15.905
because i did not
want to lose that contract.

12:15.906 --> 12:19.068
But i tell you right now,
i wanted to take my 5-iron,

12:19.069 --> 12:21.911
and i wanted to bludgeon
that son of a bitch!

12:21.912 --> 12:25.074
Wait till Laurel passes the bar
before you assault anyone.

12:25.075 --> 12:28.127
Actually, dad would be charged
with more than assault for that,

12:28.128 --> 12:32.042
probably aggravated battery
with a deadly weapon.

12:33.583 --> 12:36.295
Hmm.
Looks like someone's
learning a lot.

12:36.296 --> 12:37.506
[ Laughter ]

12:37.507 --> 12:40.179
Vanessa, whatever happened
with juanita?

12:40.180 --> 12:41.760
Do you still think
you want to replace her?

12:41.761 --> 12:43.432
I am learning a lot,

12:43.433 --> 12:45.845
especially working
with this defense attorney.

12:45.846 --> 12:48.187
She just found out her husband
killed a student

12:48.188 --> 12:50.020
who he was having
an affair with.

12:52.943 --> 12:54.733
I-is that a joke?

12:54.734 --> 12:58.487
No, he strangled her on the roof
of a sorority house

12:58.488 --> 13:00.860
and then put her
in a water tank.

13:00.861 --> 13:02.201
Now he's gone missing.

13:02.202 --> 13:03.572
This is who you've been
working for?

13:03.573 --> 13:05.454
I thought i told you.

13:05.455 --> 13:06.575
I don't remember.

13:06.576 --> 13:08.457
Oh, right.
That's 'cause you never asked.

13:08.458 --> 13:10.499
Well, actually,
she did call once

13:10.500 --> 13:13.172
to ask me if i was
dating anyone.

13:13.173 --> 13:15.414
I am, by the way...
Two guys at the same time.

13:15.415 --> 13:17.177
Jorge: Mija!

13:18.088 --> 13:21.801
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

13:34.564 --> 13:35.896
Dad...
No, no, no!

13:46.997 --> 13:48.828
Feliz navidad.

13:55.795 --> 13:56.796
[ Screams ]

14:01.381 --> 14:03.052
I know you probably
can't tell me

14:03.053 --> 14:04.633
what you're doing
about Sam's sister.

14:04.634 --> 14:06.015
You're right, so don't ask.

14:06.016 --> 14:07.596
But i was also thinking
about Connor's car.

14:07.597 --> 14:08.677
What about it?

14:08.678 --> 14:10.139
It's loaded
with forensic evidence.

14:10.140 --> 14:11.931
And no matter how many times
he gets it cleaned...

14:11.932 --> 14:14.023
This is how you get caught...
By being dumb enough to talk

14:14.024 --> 14:15.314
about any of this
inside a courthouse.

14:15.315 --> 14:17.436
So sit quiet at the kiddie table

14:17.437 --> 14:19.278
and know the adults
are taking care of things.

14:19.279 --> 14:20.900
Asher:
Oh, franky d!

14:20.901 --> 14:22.902
Hey, you want to hit up
the squeaky z tonight?

14:22.903 --> 14:25.034
Been a solid week
since we blew some backs out.

14:25.035 --> 14:26.035
It depends on work.

14:26.036 --> 14:27.907
All right, son.
You let me know, yo.

14:27.908 --> 14:29.658
Judge marber:
How does the defendant plead?

14:29.659 --> 14:31.700
No contest, your honor.

14:31.701 --> 14:36.085
However, we've entered into
a plea agreement with the d.A.

14:36.086 --> 14:37.496
What are the terms?

14:37.497 --> 14:38.958
Uh, we've agreed
on three years probation

14:38.959 --> 14:40.299
and immediate
outpatient treatment

14:40.300 --> 14:42.461
at a mental-health clinic.

14:42.462 --> 14:46.715
I can't accept this until i hear
from the victims themselves.

14:46.716 --> 14:48.057
Your honor, it would be cruel

14:48.058 --> 14:50.269
to subject these women
to open-court testimony.

14:50.270 --> 14:52.061
We'll hold an in-camera
session tomorrow.

14:52.062 --> 14:55.064
No public, no jury, no press.

14:55.065 --> 14:56.605
Next case!

14:56.606 --> 14:58.398
[ Gavel bangs ]

15:00.610 --> 15:02.231
You said I'd get out today.

15:02.232 --> 15:03.983
It's just a formality.

15:03.984 --> 15:05.985
[ Handcuffs click ]

15:05.986 --> 15:09.238
Draft questions for my
cross-examination of the girls,

15:09.239 --> 15:12.621
anything that establishes Jackie
was Vince's victim, too,

15:12.622 --> 15:15.415
and helps the judge
to accept the deal.

15:18.538 --> 15:22.131
She's a victim. That's how
the cycle of abuse works.

15:22.132 --> 15:24.344
So stop judging and do your job.

15:27.847 --> 15:29.758
I object to working on this case
on moral grounds.

15:29.759 --> 15:31.551
Then you can go work
at another law office.

15:35.015 --> 15:39.018
Really?
You're gonna fire me

15:39.019 --> 15:40.860
when i could file
a sexual-harassment suit?

15:42.322 --> 15:44.064
Oh.

16:19.559 --> 16:21.310
Do you want to come in?

16:21.311 --> 16:25.064
Who are we visiting?
Your boyfriend?

16:25.065 --> 16:27.656
Well, if you won't talk to me,

16:27.657 --> 16:29.448
i have no choice
but to find answers

16:29.449 --> 16:31.700
to my questions
in more unorthodox ways.

16:31.701 --> 16:33.112
By stalking me?

16:33.113 --> 16:35.284
Call it what you want.

16:35.285 --> 16:36.705
It must feel good, huh,

16:36.706 --> 16:38.497
knowing you were right about me
this whole time?

16:38.498 --> 16:40.419
I've only ever loved you,
Annalise.

16:40.420 --> 16:41.830
No, you just tolerated me,

16:41.831 --> 16:43.082
because you've been too busy
tearing me apart,

16:43.083 --> 16:46.085
waiting for Sam to throw out
the garbage he married.

16:46.086 --> 16:47.126
Your words reveal a lot more

16:47.127 --> 16:49.218
about what you feel about
yourself right now than me.

16:49.219 --> 16:51.130
I'm not one of your patients,

16:51.131 --> 16:54.474
so don't try to
psychoanalyze me.
God forbid, no.

16:57.187 --> 16:59.188
So, sure you don't
want to come in?

16:59.189 --> 17:02.521
No.
I'm good out here.

17:02.522 --> 17:06.405
Suit yourself.

17:06.406 --> 17:08.407
[ Dog barking in distance ]

17:08.408 --> 17:11.490
Nate: You ignored my call
on Christmas.

17:11.491 --> 17:13.702
It went to voicemail
on the second ring.

17:13.703 --> 17:17.206
And the same thing
happens on new year's.

17:17.207 --> 17:18.497
Were you busy with family?

17:18.498 --> 17:20.920
Mm.

17:24.254 --> 17:26.666
Did you spend Christmas
with Nia?

17:28.218 --> 17:30.429
Yeah.

17:30.430 --> 17:32.051
How is she?

17:36.055 --> 17:37.436
I'm sorry.

17:37.437 --> 17:39.228
We don't have to talk about her.

17:39.229 --> 17:40.849
Because you don't want to?

17:40.850 --> 17:43.142
No.

17:43.143 --> 17:45.734
No, i just...

17:45.735 --> 17:49.148
I want to talk
about whatever you want.

17:49.149 --> 17:51.950
We wanted to get her
into this clinical trial,

17:51.951 --> 17:55.115
but her numbers...
They didn't check out.

18:01.621 --> 18:04.164
I told her about you.

18:06.626 --> 18:08.917
She wants me to be happy.

18:08.918 --> 18:10.839
I said I'd tell her
the same thing

18:10.840 --> 18:12.511
if it was me in the hospital.

18:12.512 --> 18:14.634
I don't think she's right.

18:23.223 --> 18:26.025
You're very lucky you found her.

18:28.188 --> 18:32.401
[ Breathes deeply ]
Yeah.

18:32.402 --> 18:35.784
[ Wes screaming ]

18:35.785 --> 18:39.198
Wes. Shh, shh. Wes.
I know.

18:39.199 --> 18:42.201
Hey, you fell asleep
when we were studying.

18:42.202 --> 18:44.243
Which one was it?

18:44.244 --> 18:48.667
The house, woods,
Connor with a chainsaw?

18:48.668 --> 18:51.089
[ Exhales sharply ]
No.

18:51.090 --> 18:53.422
I was locked in a basement.

18:53.423 --> 18:54.463
That's good.

18:54.464 --> 18:56.385
You're moving on
to current events.

18:56.386 --> 18:57.636
No more falling asleep

18:57.637 --> 18:59.928
while you're working cases
about crazies.

18:59.929 --> 19:01.760
Palate cleanser.
Come on.

19:01.761 --> 19:04.142
[ Sighs ]

19:04.143 --> 19:05.524
Let's watch...

19:05.525 --> 19:07.767
Adorable baby animals
getting belly rubs.

19:16.446 --> 19:17.986
♪ Go get
the old chimney sweeper ♪
[ Connor roars ]

19:17.987 --> 19:20.199
Here comes Mr. sea monster,
and he's hungry for something

19:20.200 --> 19:22.160
that tastes
like little children!
♪ make sure
the chimney is clean ♪

19:22.161 --> 19:24.783
Okay, enough torturing
your uncle.

19:24.784 --> 19:26.285
Go find daddy.

19:26.286 --> 19:28.287
Go. Go!

19:28.288 --> 19:31.290
[ Both laugh ]

19:31.291 --> 19:35.504
You didn't like my present?

19:35.505 --> 19:39.007
He thinks you're gorgeous.
And honestly, isn't he?

19:39.008 --> 19:42.261
Yeah. I'm just
trying to be good.

19:42.262 --> 19:44.933
[ Laughs ]
You, good?

19:44.934 --> 19:47.266
[ Laughs ]

19:47.267 --> 19:49.067
What is it?

19:49.068 --> 19:51.480
Tell me so i can help.

19:51.481 --> 19:54.112
♪ And Christmas is in the air ♪

19:54.113 --> 19:55.274
[ Inhales sharply ]

19:55.275 --> 19:57.366
♪ I pray when we come together ♪

19:57.367 --> 19:59.117
Um...

19:59.118 --> 20:00.909
♪ Our loved ones
will all be there ♪

20:00.910 --> 20:03.872
just i-i-i have
a boyfriend.

20:03.873 --> 20:05.163
What?! Who?

20:05.164 --> 20:08.587
Uh, his... his name is Oliver,
and it's... it's really new,

20:08.588 --> 20:10.379
and i don't want to make a big
deal of it, so just don't...

20:10.380 --> 20:11.540
Don't tell mom.

20:11.541 --> 20:12.671
Oh, god, no.

20:12.672 --> 20:14.253
She'd probably start
planning the wedding.

20:14.254 --> 20:15.294
Gross.

20:15.295 --> 20:17.175
[ Laughs ]

20:17.176 --> 20:19.888
What?
Hmm. Nothing.

20:19.889 --> 20:25.104
Just... My slutty little brother
is finally growing up.

20:33.903 --> 20:36.485
My grandma made it.

20:36.486 --> 20:37.736
So this is a regift?

20:37.737 --> 20:42.071
I couldn't pull it off,
but you totally can.

20:44.243 --> 20:47.456
Oh, yeah!
Look at that!

20:47.457 --> 20:48.747
All right, grab your coat.

20:48.748 --> 20:50.369
We're gonna be late for
our reservation at moretti's.

20:50.370 --> 20:52.581
What are you talking about?
It's like zero degrees out.

20:52.582 --> 20:54.333
You'll be happy
you're wearing your hat.

20:54.334 --> 20:58.136
No, no. I...
I mean, what are you doing,

20:58.137 --> 20:59.298
bringing me gifts

20:59.299 --> 21:02.180
and making reservations
at fancy restaurants?

21:02.181 --> 21:06.385
Well...
I-i like you,

21:06.386 --> 21:09.097
and i want to spend time
with you.

21:09.098 --> 21:12.441
I can't, not tonight.

21:12.442 --> 21:13.852
I-i already
rented a movie,

21:13.853 --> 21:16.064
and it's gonna expire
if i don't watch it.

21:16.065 --> 21:18.066
Okay, yeah.
I'm down for a night in.

21:18.067 --> 21:19.739
I didn't invite you to stay.

21:21.160 --> 21:23.822
We're not dating.

21:23.823 --> 21:24.993
And last i heard,

21:24.994 --> 21:26.325
you were supposed to be dealing
with your drug problem.

21:26.326 --> 21:28.327
I haven't used since that night.

21:28.328 --> 21:31.790
Well, yeah, because you were
on vacation without any school

21:31.791 --> 21:33.962
or crazy professors making you
work 40 hours a week.

21:33.963 --> 21:36.545
I'm not... [ Sighs ]

21:36.546 --> 21:38.467
I'm not gonna freak out again.

21:38.468 --> 21:40.469
I promise.

21:40.470 --> 21:42.130
Look, if you kick me out
right now,

21:42.131 --> 21:44.012
i can't guarantee
that I'm not gonna go

21:44.013 --> 21:46.095
straight to a dealer
and buy an eight ball.

21:48.267 --> 21:50.188
Fine.

21:50.189 --> 21:53.392
But you stay on your end
of the couch.

21:53.393 --> 21:55.985
And you can't laugh
at what i rented.

21:57.777 --> 21:59.988
Uh, what's "the Thorn birds"?

21:59.989 --> 22:02.071
What did i say?
[ Laughs ]

22:12.081 --> 22:14.584
[ Sniffs ]

22:17.126 --> 22:19.167
What the...

22:19.168 --> 22:21.049
My car was stolen.

22:21.050 --> 22:22.461
What?
Are you kidding?

22:22.462 --> 22:24.553
You think i would make a joke
about this, Michaela?

22:24.554 --> 22:25.634
You didn't tell the police?

22:25.635 --> 22:26.885
No, i didn't tell the police.

22:26.886 --> 22:28.266
Obviously, i can't.

22:28.267 --> 22:29.678
There's traces of...
You know.

22:29.679 --> 22:31.230
Ask frank what you should do.

22:32.271 --> 22:34.232
Does anyone else think
it's weird

22:34.233 --> 22:35.814
that those two are butt buddies?

22:35.815 --> 22:37.736
And we're murderers.
Big whoop.

22:37.737 --> 22:40.318
Frank.

22:40.319 --> 22:42.691
So, uh, my...
My car was stolen.

22:42.692 --> 22:45.243
Bummer.
You report it to the police?

22:45.244 --> 22:48.076
No.

22:48.077 --> 22:50.749
Do you think i should?

22:50.750 --> 22:52.992
Don't you want
the insurance money?

22:58.087 --> 23:02.921
Was there a time that you saw
Jackie's husband hurt her?

23:02.922 --> 23:05.213
Yes.

23:05.214 --> 23:06.965
And did she ever hurt you?

23:06.966 --> 23:11.139
She was always nice,
like a mother.

23:11.140 --> 23:13.351
Did Jackie
ever try to help you...

23:13.352 --> 23:15.353
Bring you food, clothing?

23:15.354 --> 23:17.606
She snuck us things
when she could.

23:17.607 --> 23:21.359
I like to crochet,
so she'd bring me yarn.

23:21.360 --> 23:23.151
Was Jackie ever there
during the times

23:23.152 --> 23:27.365
that Mr. groves visited you
at night?

23:27.366 --> 23:30.949
No, but she would
visit us before,

23:30.950 --> 23:33.161
give us milk.

23:33.162 --> 23:34.953
She said it would help
put us to sleep

23:34.954 --> 23:39.669
so we wouldn't have to...
Know what he was doing.

23:44.714 --> 23:46.304
Annalise:
You drugged them?!

23:46.305 --> 23:48.176
I was trying to help them.

23:48.177 --> 23:49.968
By helping your husband
rape those girls,

23:49.969 --> 23:51.139
making them pliable.

23:51.140 --> 23:52.892
You've never been raped,
have you?

23:54.644 --> 23:58.687
Because i have been,

23:58.688 --> 24:03.361
by him, before him, as a child.

24:03.362 --> 24:06.655
The memory of that is worse
than what happens to you.

24:06.656 --> 24:10.869
So, yes,
i helped put them to sleep,

24:10.870 --> 24:14.203
but only so they wouldn't
have the memories.

24:18.538 --> 24:21.750
So she drugged these girls,
lied to us about it,

24:21.751 --> 24:23.171
and we still haven't
dropped the case.

24:23.172 --> 24:25.173
Remind me why.
This isn't a democracy.

24:25.174 --> 24:26.424
If Annalise believes a client

24:26.425 --> 24:28.216
is worth saving,
then we save her.

24:28.217 --> 24:29.588
Huh, you know,
that would have sounded

24:29.589 --> 24:32.221
a hell of a lot more convincing
coming out of a.K.'S mouth.

24:34.013 --> 24:36.014
Look into the evidence
they found at the house,

24:36.015 --> 24:37.225
the girls' testimony.

24:37.226 --> 24:38.057
Just find us something

24:38.058 --> 24:40.019
that will help us go back
to the judge.

24:48.027 --> 24:50.448
Good work with Connor's car.

24:50.449 --> 24:52.611
What do you mean?
He find it?

24:52.612 --> 24:55.664
No, and he won't,
because you stole it

24:55.665 --> 24:58.206
and probably already
had it destroyed.

24:58.207 --> 25:00.038
It's also why you're hanging out
with Asher.

25:00.039 --> 25:01.620
In case he starts
getting suspicious,

25:01.621 --> 25:03.121
"keep your enemies close"
type thing.

25:03.122 --> 25:06.004
You've got quite an imagination.

25:06.005 --> 25:07.385
Mm.

25:07.386 --> 25:09.798
Whatever.
Take my ideas.

25:09.799 --> 25:12.130
Just don't say i don't deserve

25:12.131 --> 25:14.092
to be in
the grown-up table.

25:14.093 --> 25:15.935
Okay?

25:17.516 --> 25:21.059
Jackie: Last time, he wouldn't
let us go to a hospital,

25:21.060 --> 25:22.901
and our little girl
was stillborn.

25:22.902 --> 25:26.696
I can't let that happen again.
Lynn deserves to keep this one.

25:29.068 --> 25:32.861
Our little girl was stillborn.
I can't let that happen again.

25:32.862 --> 25:36.364
Lynn deserves to keep this one.

25:36.365 --> 25:39.537
Lynn deserves to keep this one.

25:39.538 --> 25:41.289
Dude, this isn't a remix
I'm really down with.

25:41.290 --> 25:43.041
What if she kept the baby?

25:43.042 --> 25:45.083
What do you mean?
She says, "our little girl."

25:45.084 --> 25:48.086
Like the baby's hers, too,

25:48.087 --> 25:51.299
and, "Lynn deserves
to keep this one."

25:51.300 --> 25:54.723
Maybe the other one was taken
from her.

25:54.724 --> 25:56.805
That baby is alive, isn't she?

25:56.806 --> 26:00.228
That's why you wanted a plea
where you serve no time...

26:00.229 --> 26:03.773
Because you're raising the baby
you told Lynn was born dead.

26:04.814 --> 26:06.985
Admit it!

26:06.986 --> 26:10.398
She's my little girl.

26:10.399 --> 26:12.531
[ Voice breaking ]
And i love her.

26:16.195 --> 26:18.576
Where is she, Jackie?

26:18.577 --> 26:21.000
Tell me right now.

26:23.162 --> 26:26.374
Get me my plea deal.

26:26.375 --> 26:29.378
Then I'll tell you where she is.

26:37.677 --> 26:40.058
I'll swing by the house tomorrow
and check it out.

26:40.059 --> 26:42.060
Yeah, merry whatever
to you, too.

26:42.061 --> 26:44.062
Oh, who is that?

26:44.063 --> 26:46.024
Bonnie.
Ah.

26:46.025 --> 26:47.776
She stay in town
or she go visit her family?

26:47.777 --> 26:49.778
Nah, her family's messed up.

26:49.779 --> 26:51.149
What do you care?

26:51.150 --> 26:52.731
I don't.

26:52.732 --> 26:54.112
Just we all work together,

26:54.113 --> 26:56.034
and we barely know anything
about her.

26:56.035 --> 26:58.997
So her family's messed up?

26:58.998 --> 27:02.741
What the hell?
You into her?

27:02.742 --> 27:06.164
[ Scoffs ] No!
God no!

27:06.165 --> 27:08.126
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:08.127 --> 27:09.127
[ Laughter ]

27:09.128 --> 27:10.959
How would you like
to ride my pony?

27:10.960 --> 27:13.051
Oh! Mmm!

27:13.052 --> 27:14.212
Don't go there.

27:14.213 --> 27:17.095
Why not, man?
She's at least a... Six.

27:17.096 --> 27:19.467
She'll send you to the doctor
unless you double wrap.

27:19.468 --> 27:21.059
Trust me.

27:21.060 --> 27:23.061
Well, at least we'd be
eskimo bros, then.

27:23.062 --> 27:24.062
Am i right?

27:24.063 --> 27:25.815
[ Bottles clink ]
Unh.

27:27.977 --> 27:29.688
I'll be there in 20.

27:29.689 --> 27:31.229
Ow!

27:31.230 --> 27:36.034
I'm staging a walkout.
Here we go.

27:36.035 --> 27:37.656
Follow me!

27:38.828 --> 27:40.658
Except for you.

27:40.659 --> 27:42.581
We know you don't
have the balls.

27:44.123 --> 27:46.915
Over here.
You can't interfere with
my legal right to protest.

27:46.916 --> 27:48.998
Now.

27:50.209 --> 27:52.841
I crossed a line with you, yes,

27:52.842 --> 27:54.132
but we are both
professionals here,

27:54.133 --> 27:55.133
and you need to grow up
and start respecting me

27:55.134 --> 27:57.505
if we are gonna keep...
You hurt my feelings...

27:57.506 --> 27:59.637
A lot.

27:59.638 --> 28:01.139
And i know
i should be used to it now,

28:01.140 --> 28:02.721
because everyone here
makes fun of me all the time,

28:02.722 --> 28:06.265
but you didn't, and then you
were mean to me for no reason.

28:09.108 --> 28:14.023
Yeah, whatever.
I'll... I'll stop being a jerk.

28:15.815 --> 28:18.616
Your husband told us
the baby died two months ago.

28:18.617 --> 28:20.198
Because that's what i told him.

28:20.199 --> 28:22.490
She'd just turned 4,

28:22.491 --> 28:25.703
and i saw the way he started
looking at her.

28:25.704 --> 28:27.415
I couldn't let that happen.

28:27.416 --> 28:33.131
So i told him she died
and that i took care of it.

28:33.132 --> 28:36.835
Then...
Why turn him in?

28:36.836 --> 28:38.426
You kept that child safe.

28:38.427 --> 28:40.839
Because of Lynn.

28:40.840 --> 28:43.141
She's about to deliver,

28:43.142 --> 28:49.308
and i-i want her to know how
amazing it is to be a mother.

28:52.111 --> 28:53.691
What's the baby's name?

28:53.692 --> 28:55.984
Heather.

28:55.985 --> 29:01.069
Is someone with Heather?
Is she being taken care of?

29:01.070 --> 29:05.703
She has a buddy, a giraffe,

29:05.704 --> 29:09.077
that she talks to
when she is scared at night.

29:09.078 --> 29:11.669
She knows mommy
always comes back.

29:11.670 --> 29:15.795
I thought I'd be back.

29:20.009 --> 29:23.011
Thank god i don't have a gun,
or else I'd shoot her myself.

29:23.012 --> 29:25.143
She didn't tell you
where she is?

29:25.144 --> 29:27.385
No, not unless a deal is
on the table. Where's the d.A.?

29:27.386 --> 29:28.597
He's just around the corner.

29:34.814 --> 29:37.605
[ Sighs ]
Congratulations.

29:37.606 --> 29:39.197
The d.A. Gave you
what you want...

29:39.198 --> 29:42.861
No jail time
and a suspended sentence.

29:42.862 --> 29:45.453
Now give us her location.

29:45.454 --> 29:47.705
But I'll never see her again.

29:47.706 --> 29:49.207
This is what you wanted, Jackie!

29:49.208 --> 29:51.079
No, i wanted to be back
with her.

29:51.080 --> 29:54.502
She's my daughter.
The rest of this...

29:54.503 --> 29:56.084
[ Breathing heavily ]

29:56.085 --> 29:58.006
You claim you're not a monster.

29:58.007 --> 30:01.339
Don't be as bad as him.

30:01.340 --> 30:05.014
Protect the only innocent person
left in all of this filth.

30:08.057 --> 30:11.059
[ Voice breaking ] She's in
a cabin my aunt owned...

30:11.060 --> 30:14.643
9123 mayersville road.

30:17.987 --> 30:19.358
[ Sobs ]

30:33.212 --> 30:36.005
[ Door opens ]

30:59.608 --> 31:02.110
Laurel:
So, we need to talk.

31:02.111 --> 31:03.481
We can't just go back
to being strangers

31:03.482 --> 31:04.822
like nothing ever happened.

31:04.823 --> 31:07.245
This is stupid.
I'm going inside.
Michaela.

31:07.246 --> 31:08.536
What happened to you
over the break?

31:08.537 --> 31:11.869
Everything can't be as perfect
as you said.

31:11.870 --> 31:12.911
I'm fine.

31:12.912 --> 31:14.752
No, you're pretending
to be fine.

31:14.753 --> 31:16.584
But how could you
after what we did?

31:16.585 --> 31:18.796
That's enough group therapy
for me.

31:18.797 --> 31:20.798
Connor,
unless we all start talking,

31:20.799 --> 31:22.500
we are all gonna fall apart,

31:22.501 --> 31:25.094
and that is exactly how
we're gonna end up in jail.

31:27.716 --> 31:30.929
I got back together with kan.

31:30.930 --> 31:32.931
I am trying to get over frank.

31:32.932 --> 31:35.893
I saw my family over the break.
It was the worst thing ever.

31:35.894 --> 31:39.018
So i actually missed you guys.

31:41.150 --> 31:43.361
You...
What's going on with you?

31:43.362 --> 31:47.866
I can't sleep
without having nightmares.

31:50.909 --> 31:53.701
I'm scared
i might be going crazy.

31:53.702 --> 31:58.296
Great. That's great.
[ Scoffs ]

31:58.297 --> 32:01.249
Connor...
No. [ Scoffs ]

32:01.250 --> 32:04.802
Look, you wanted to talk.

32:04.803 --> 32:08.216
Let's talk about how you lied
to Michaela and me,

32:08.217 --> 32:09.387
how you sold us out to Annalise.

32:09.388 --> 32:11.809
You want to talk about that?
Don't drag me into this.

32:11.810 --> 32:14.182
No, we're on the same team,
Michaela.

32:14.183 --> 32:15.553
But these two... i mean,
w-w-what did Annalise call them,

32:15.554 --> 32:18.016
the... the... the quiet ones,
the dangerous ones?

32:18.017 --> 32:20.518
I mean, for all we know,
they're still playing us.

32:20.519 --> 32:21.729
Playing you?
See? You just proved my point.

32:21.730 --> 32:23.731
That is exactly
why we have to talk.

32:23.732 --> 32:26.774
I don't want to tell you people
anything about myself!

32:26.775 --> 32:29.777
Okay, fine. But then you can't
secretly hate us, okay?

32:29.778 --> 32:31.739
Because that is exactly

32:31.740 --> 32:33.872
how we're gonna
end up getting caught.

32:36.415 --> 32:41.169
Fine. We talked.
I'm going inside.

32:41.170 --> 32:43.582
What's going on here?

32:44.543 --> 32:46.174
Hi.

32:46.175 --> 32:49.138
I'm Hannah, Sam's sister.

32:50.259 --> 32:53.262
Who are all of you?

33:02.191 --> 33:03.901
[ Indistinct conversations ]

33:03.902 --> 33:07.985
♪ The snow is snowing,
candlelight is glowing ♪

33:07.986 --> 33:12.820
♪ it is Christmas time
at last ♪

33:12.821 --> 33:14.872
[ Laughing ]

33:14.873 --> 33:17.615
♪ Christmas time,
love is everywhere ♪

33:17.616 --> 33:19.877
♪ with someone who loves me ♪
that was the best thing...

33:19.878 --> 33:22.120
What's going on?
Michaela.

33:22.121 --> 33:24.752
Who are you?
Michaela, stop.

33:24.753 --> 33:27.125
Are you two screwing?
Excuse me?

33:27.126 --> 33:28.966
Michaela,
this is Holden wescott.

33:28.967 --> 33:31.049
We worked together
on the mayor's campaign.

33:31.050 --> 33:34.092
♪ Twelve o'clock Christmas Eve ♪

33:34.093 --> 33:35.723
What is wrong with you?

33:35.724 --> 33:37.225
I don't know.
I just...

33:37.226 --> 33:38.806
[ inhales sharply ]

33:38.807 --> 33:41.018
Everything at school
is really hard.

33:41.019 --> 33:43.601
What does that
have to do with me?
It doesn't. I just... i...

33:43.602 --> 33:44.982
You just humiliated me
in front of a colleague.

33:44.983 --> 33:47.195
Oh, god.
I had too much champagne.

33:47.196 --> 33:49.197
That only explains it
if this was the first

33:49.198 --> 33:50.908
crazy thing
that you've done this trip.

33:50.909 --> 33:53.281
You slept the entire time
at my parents' house.

33:53.282 --> 33:55.863
I had to convince my mother
not to call a psychiatrist,

33:55.864 --> 33:57.865
which now i think
we should have done.

33:57.866 --> 33:59.247
Okay.

33:59.248 --> 34:01.459
I'll be better.
I promise.

34:01.460 --> 34:04.252
No, no. No,
i can't do this anymore.

34:04.253 --> 34:05.874
What?!

34:08.297 --> 34:10.718
I think we should postpone
the wedding.

34:10.719 --> 34:13.131
[ Scoffs ]

34:13.132 --> 34:14.172
No.

34:14.173 --> 34:16.384
[ Laughs ] No!

34:16.385 --> 34:18.096
No, no!

34:18.097 --> 34:19.227
Don't...
Don't do this.

34:19.228 --> 34:21.769
I swear I'll do anything
you want.

34:21.770 --> 34:25.143
Just don't...
Don't do this.

34:25.144 --> 34:26.684
[ Voice breaking ]
I love you.

34:26.685 --> 34:30.898
I want to marry you,
and you want to marry me.

34:30.899 --> 34:33.691
[ Sighs ] No.

34:33.692 --> 34:36.744
No, i don't...

34:36.745 --> 34:39.076
Not when you're like this.

34:39.077 --> 34:41.699
I'm sorry.

34:41.700 --> 34:42.910
No.
I'm sorry.

34:42.911 --> 34:47.084
No, no. Aiden...

34:47.085 --> 34:48.506
[ Screams ]

34:48.507 --> 34:49.757
Laurel: Michaela.

34:49.758 --> 34:51.088
M-m-m-m-my ring.

34:51.089 --> 34:54.262
I will let Annalise know
you stopped by.

34:54.263 --> 34:56.093
Oh, good.

34:56.094 --> 34:59.807
And tell her none of that
was as helpful as I'd hoped.

34:59.808 --> 35:03.431
Not one girl
in that sorority house

35:03.432 --> 35:06.224
saw him go upstairs
to the roof that night.

35:06.225 --> 35:10.027
And what about the fact
that Sam's DNA

35:10.028 --> 35:12.029
was nowhere on that girl?

35:12.030 --> 35:14.612
Annalise would be able to
get this case thrown out

35:14.613 --> 35:16.535
with her eyes closed.

35:18.036 --> 35:22.660
Please, Bonnie, help me.

35:22.661 --> 35:26.664
Help me figure out
what's going on here.

35:26.665 --> 35:29.878
I know how special you were
to Sam.

35:35.754 --> 35:38.217
You should go.

35:45.063 --> 35:48.186
Annalise:
They found Heather.

35:48.187 --> 35:49.977
She was dehydrated
and malnourished,

35:49.978 --> 35:51.939
but she's okay.
Oh, thank god!

35:51.940 --> 35:55.403
[ Sobs ]
She's with Lynn.

35:55.404 --> 35:56.574
It's good they have each other
to get through this.

35:56.575 --> 36:02.660
I know i can't see her,
but maybe when she's 18,

36:02.661 --> 36:05.243
once she understands
why i did this,

36:05.244 --> 36:07.124
she'll want to see me again.

36:07.125 --> 36:09.497
You won't be out of jail
by then.

36:09.498 --> 36:14.922
But I'm not going to jail.
I have a deal.

36:14.923 --> 36:17.505
I said you had a deal,

36:17.506 --> 36:20.848
but no one was here to testify
to that fact, just you and me,

36:20.849 --> 36:23.971
and you're not the only
good liar in this room.

36:23.972 --> 36:26.974
I've withdrawn as your lawyer.

36:26.975 --> 36:28.976
Good luck finding a new one.

36:28.977 --> 36:30.398
♪ I salute you, Christopher ♪

36:30.399 --> 36:31.729
Connor:
If I'm being honest,

36:31.730 --> 36:34.111
i looked forward
to "the Thorn birds" all day.

36:34.112 --> 36:36.734
♪ I salute your life ♪
didn't school start again?

36:36.735 --> 36:39.317
I mean, don't you have to
go home and do work?

36:39.318 --> 36:42.119
♪ How you played the dice ♪
well, yeah, but, you know,
it's the first week,

36:42.120 --> 36:45.663
and i have to find out if Ralph
and meggie finally do it.

36:45.664 --> 36:49.667
♪ Your words will live in us ♪

36:49.668 --> 36:51.419
♪ timelessly insane ♪

36:51.420 --> 36:53.421
You don't get to do that.

36:53.422 --> 36:56.133
Uh... You kissed me.

36:56.134 --> 36:58.426
Exactly.
I'm so stupid.

36:58.427 --> 36:59.887
Look, Oliver, relax, okay?

36:59.888 --> 37:01.549
No.
Don't you get it?

37:01.550 --> 37:04.932
You... you go through life
looking like you do,

37:04.933 --> 37:07.104
meeting guys all the time,
but me...

37:07.105 --> 37:09.607
You're...
You were special to me,

37:09.608 --> 37:11.439
and then you hooked up
with that other guy.

37:11.440 --> 37:13.110
Look, Oliver,
i-i really like you, too.

37:13.111 --> 37:14.482
I more than like you!

37:14.483 --> 37:16.113
Damn it.

37:16.114 --> 37:21.068
Like... You know the way
that you can't do drugs?

37:21.069 --> 37:22.990
That's how you are for me.

37:22.991 --> 37:26.033
Look, we can...
We can take this slow.

37:26.034 --> 37:28.165
Just...

37:28.166 --> 37:33.040
I don't trust anyone
in my life right now except you.

37:33.041 --> 37:39.177
So just don't...
Don't make me go, please.

37:41.139 --> 37:45.092
The New York call cost us more
money than i first thought.

37:45.093 --> 37:48.936
Still, i think it got them off
the scent for a few days.

37:48.937 --> 37:50.598
They have a lead on Sam.

37:50.599 --> 37:53.601
A police officer's wife called
from upstate New York

37:53.602 --> 37:55.563
and said she thinks she saw him
at a rest stop.

37:55.564 --> 38:00.198
Thank you for taking care
of that for me.

38:01.700 --> 38:04.492
Anything else?

38:04.493 --> 38:07.905
I know you said not to worry,

38:07.906 --> 38:10.498
but she's snooping
around everywhere.

38:10.499 --> 38:12.710
It's making the kids
freak out a bit.

38:12.711 --> 38:14.712
Well, tell them not to do that.

38:14.713 --> 38:17.044
I will.

38:17.045 --> 38:19.177
But she wants answers, Annalise.

38:21.920 --> 38:26.303
You want me to handle it,
just say the word.

38:26.304 --> 38:28.926
No.

38:28.927 --> 38:31.689
I can take care of it myself.

38:31.690 --> 38:34.692
♪ I salute you, Christopher ♪

38:34.693 --> 38:40.778
♪ i salute your life ♪

38:40.779 --> 38:46.364
♪ how you played the dice ♪

38:46.365 --> 38:50.037
Can't remember the last time
i saw you cook.

38:50.038 --> 38:53.001
Me neither.

38:56.044 --> 38:57.625
Brussels sprouts?

38:57.626 --> 39:01.759
Seriously, is that what we're
doing... Brussels sprouts?

39:01.760 --> 39:04.011
All right?
I-i got the call.

39:04.012 --> 39:07.224
I thought you invited me here
and that we might talk...

39:07.225 --> 39:08.136
Actually talk.

39:08.137 --> 39:09.597
I'm trying here, Hannah.

39:09.598 --> 39:11.519
No, you're not.
You're hiding, Annalise.

39:11.520 --> 39:15.893
You're hiding, when a man we
both love is missing or worse.

39:15.894 --> 39:18.025
And yet you just hide
behind this wall.

39:18.026 --> 39:20.438
Just because I'm not behaving
in the way you would...

39:20.439 --> 39:22.860
I am not asking you to cry
on my shoulder, Annalise!

39:22.861 --> 39:24.111
I am asking you
to be a real person!

39:24.112 --> 39:25.533
I am who i am.

39:25.534 --> 39:27.364
If you don't like it,
i don't care.

39:27.365 --> 39:28.786
Oh, you do care.

39:28.787 --> 39:31.789
Otherwise, you wouldn't be
so busy avoiding me

39:31.790 --> 39:33.451
so that i couldn't
see through you

39:33.452 --> 39:36.163
to see what this performance
is all about.

39:36.164 --> 39:37.125
Sam felt it, too.

39:37.126 --> 39:39.126
But you know what?
I'm done with it.

39:39.127 --> 39:42.761
I'm done with it!
I want the truth!

39:53.562 --> 39:56.143
All right, go ahead.
You want the truth?

39:56.144 --> 39:57.225
Go ahead and ask me.

39:59.017 --> 40:01.859
When did you start
sleeping with Nate?

40:01.860 --> 40:04.442
This summer.

40:04.443 --> 40:07.234
He was one of the detectives
on my case.

40:07.235 --> 40:11.078
We met up at the courthouse
the next day, had drinks.

40:11.079 --> 40:13.330
And that was after Sam
was sleeping with Lila.

40:13.331 --> 40:15.493
When did you find out
about Lila?

40:15.494 --> 40:17.836
Three months ago.

40:20.799 --> 40:23.801
You told the police it was after
he'd already disappeared.

40:23.802 --> 40:25.844
I lied.

40:28.096 --> 40:33.310
I was already representing
Rebecca when i saw the photos,

40:33.311 --> 40:35.723
him on Lila's phone,

40:35.724 --> 40:38.686
and i did everything i could
to cover his tracks.

40:38.687 --> 40:40.107
I got rid of evidence.

40:40.108 --> 40:42.439
I did things that would have
ruined my practice,

40:42.440 --> 40:44.942
got me arrested.

40:44.943 --> 40:47.616
I tried to help him, Hannah.

40:57.205 --> 40:58.786
You know, all this time,

40:58.787 --> 41:03.380
i was praying that you were
hiding him somewhere,

41:03.381 --> 41:06.043
that all of this vilifying him
in public,

41:06.044 --> 41:09.547
this avoiding me
was just a ruse,

41:09.548 --> 41:14.302
that you were covering,
that you had him someplace safe.

41:16.645 --> 41:20.148
That's not true, is it?

41:24.102 --> 41:26.905
He's gone.

41:31.109 --> 41:35.282
♪ No submit, no compromise ♪

41:35.283 --> 41:39.076
♪ Saint Christopher
of the truth ♪

41:39.077 --> 41:42.169
Wes: Hey, guess what i bought
on the way home.

41:42.170 --> 41:45.172
It's, uh, a cd of ocean sounds.

41:45.173 --> 41:47.174
Apparently, if you play it,

41:47.175 --> 41:50.127
you dream of oceans
and mermaids,

41:50.128 --> 41:51.889
and you don't have nightmares

41:51.890 --> 41:54.181
[ TV chatter ]
Where dead people
chase you through the woods.

41:54.182 --> 41:55.763
Wes, we have a real nightmare.

41:55.764 --> 41:57.224
[ Keyboard clacking ]
Woman:
The human remains were found

41:57.225 --> 41:58.395
one week ago at the landfill.

41:58.396 --> 42:00.227
And although police
have yet to come forward

42:00.228 --> 42:01.398
with a public statement,

42:01.399 --> 42:04.401
our sources tell us
the body belongs

42:04.402 --> 42:07.064
to middleton university
professor Sam keating,

42:07.065 --> 42:10.487
reported missing by his wife
on December the 13th.
♪ i salute you, Christopher ♪

42:10.488 --> 42:13.110
Mr. keating is also wanted
for questioning

42:13.111 --> 42:15.492
in the murder investigation
of Lila stangard.
♪ i declare you as our king ♪

42:15.493 --> 42:17.074
Right now, police are still

42:17.075 --> 42:18.535
trying to determine the cause...

42:18.536 --> 42:22.791
♪ Or queen, depending
on your mood ♪
